    "updated_at": "2015-05-05T18:20:49Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I don't like the idea of us providing an official portable windows version, but we have added features (like the support directory override) for any downstream packagers that may want to do this.  We also make it very easy anybody to compile OpenRA from source (download the source archive, and then run make.cmd, then choose dependencies and then all) if they don't want to use the installer.\n\nOne of the headline features of the next release will be improved integration with the host OS via file and url registrations.  This is done under windows by having the installer add entries into the registry.\n"
  },
