    "created_at": "2015-05-06T00:32:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-05-06T00:32:58Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> we had to constantly tell people not to do a portable install into %ProgramFiles when you need admin rights to write in there\n\nI can think of several simple solutions to this off the top of my head:\n- File system virtualization _should_ deal with this. It should have dealt with it when the issue came up, though, so I'm not sure what's going on here.\n- Copy data to %AppData% if the folder isn't writable, and check there too.\n- [Have the installer set the Support (or main program folder) folder writable](http://nsis.sourceforge.net/AccessControl_plug-in) by all like Steam does. This might be the best solution.I'll see if I can do it myself.\n"
  },
